Model

data.json

The file path to the STL object and meta-information is specified as follows in the "data.json" file:

{

    "stlpath": "models/trouser_clip.stl",

    "objtitle": "Trouser Clip",

    "description": "A nifty little mechanism to guard your trousers from the chain grease. Order this printed in ABS to take advantage of the flexible nature of this material.",

    "materials": ["ABS","PLA","NYLON"],

    "price": 9.99,

    "price_subtext": "+ $20 for shipping outside USA."

}

 

The following code snippet from object_viewer.js refers to it like so:

...
$.getJSON("data.json",function(ajaxresult){
            //3D Object loading
            loadModelByPath(ajaxresult.stlpath);
            ...

The call to loadModelByPath is handled as follows:

    function loadModelByPath($path) {
        viewer.enableDefaultInputHandler(true);
        viewer.replaceSceneFromUrl($path);
        viewer.update();
    }

 

Intended implementation pipeline on a PHP application stack:
>> STL files are stored on server side
>> PHP script calculates volume, bouding box and price information from STL file
>> data.json file is created by a PHP script on the server
>> data.json file is loaded by STL 3D Viewer app to display object and meta-information

 

 

 

View

3D View

  • STL ASCII and Binary files are supported
  • Light-weight HTML5/Canvas based 3D renderer
  • Mouse based interactions (mouse hover activated transparent overlay)
  • Wireframe, points and flat rendering modes

 

Customize the appearance of the 3D Viewer and default rendering options by:

Editing the following lines in object_viewer.js

    function loadFromJSON() {
        $.getJSON("data_dragon.json",function(ajaxresult){
            //3D Object loading
            loadModelByPath(ajaxresult.stlpath);
            viewer.setParameter('InitRotationX', 20);
            viewer.setParameter('InitRotationY', 20);
            viewer.setParameter('InitRotationZ', 0);
            viewer.setParameter('ModelColor', '#7fca18');
            viewer.setParameter('BackgroundColor1', '#FFFFFF');
            viewer.setParameter('BackgroundColor2', '#FFFFFF');
            viewer.setParameter('RenderMode', 'flat');
            viewer.setParameter('Definition', 'high');
            viewer.init();
            viewer.update();

 

Meta-information Display
  • Object title
  • Brief description
  • Material choice button group
  • Price
  • Price sub-text



	Edit these values by manipulating data.json as explained in the "Model" module.
